s4855: Eighteenth year: Qi Tian Wu Yu came to send a daughter.
s4857: Chu Ling Wang Wei first year: Gong Wang's son, Zhou Yu.
s4870: Ninth year: Yan Ying sent to Jin, saw Shu Xiang, said 'Qi government belongs to the Tian clan.' Shu Xiang said: 'The Jin ducal house is humble.'
s4879: Twenty-seventh year: in summer went to Jin. In winter went to Chu.
s4880: Sixth year: the duke wished to kill the nobles and establish his favorite minister, the nobles executed the favorite minister, the duke feared, fled to Qi.
s4885: Fourth year: claimed illness, did not assemble with Chu.
s4889: Third year: in summer, united the feudal lords at Song territory, made alliance. Attacked Wu at Zhu Fang, executed Qing Feng. In winter, repaid us, took three cities.
s4891: Sixth year: claimed illness, did not assemble with Chu.
s4894: Seventeenth year: claimed illness, did not assemble with Chu.
s4895: Twenty-eighth year: Zi Chan said: the three states will not assemble.
s4897: Tenth year: Chu executed Qing Feng.
s4903: Twenty-first year: Qin Hou Zi returned to Qin.
s4904: Fortieth year: the duke died. Hou Zi returned from Jin.
s4905: Fourth year: led the feudal lords to attack Wu.
s4913: Eleventh year: Chu led the feudal lords to attack us.
s4918: Twelfth year: the duke went to Jin, requested to attack Yan, entered their ruler.
s4919: Twenty-second year: Qi Jing Gong came, requested to attack Yan, entered their ruler.
s4921: Fifth year: attacked Wu, camped at Qian Xi.
